item.title: Goodbye, 2009
item.description:
Goodbye, 2009
Barack Obama came to us and said he offered Change And we fiddled our thumbs for his first year and here we are again; the same And when Iran began to kill it's people No one here in America cried Because we were all out of tears From back when Michael Jackson died And crashed all of the internets With his historic worth And polls have show that Fewer people care about the earth "Global Warming's just a myth" they say, as the fish circle their feet In the water that was once ice Now melted from the heat And the GOP says "listen to me We got us a climate gate Some people wrote some emails Now the science is somehow flawed So kiss a baby, wave a flag, a praise Almighty GAWD!" And we're all supposed to be impressed That the president is black And forget, I guess, that tiny fact That he failed to get us out of Iraq And Gitmo is still open despite his promises to close it And he sent more troops to Afghanistan And the progressives all go "oh shit We seem to have elected a Bush Disguised in black sheeps clothing Shall we try to force him to stand tall Or just wallow in our self loathing?" And then they say, "Remember this: We are not fond of cowering But we're so full of cowardice That even this lame duck is empowering" And the healthcare bill started off so great With a public option for all Until the republicans snipped a string And we watched the public option fall And the democrats passed it anyway A bill riddled with compromise The bill we'll eventually get is: "Your family get's a dollar if you die." And as the tea parties rage outside With conservative nutjobs shouting "Socialism!" I wonder if someone will counter them And begin to close the schism But I have no hope, because I see Everywhere I look Signs of untamed idiocy After all, this is the year that Sarah Palin wrote a book So to summarize for all my friends We were beaten senseless and blind By a plethora of sources in The year 2009 And further, I must tell you this My colleagues, allies, and friends That we're going to do it all again In the year 2010
